pan class=title> Re: Amendment to the Raid Template -- Request</span><hr size=1> I beg to differ friend.... As leading 3 raids so far, for me as leader and having people sign up or be put on list, There will always be a few that cant make it at the last min or whatever the reason may be. So if those few didnt show then they could be quickly replaced. If raids that were sign up only and have a dead line that must be abidded by then we will have some raids that will get cancelled. Maybe too many.<br>
It really all depends on what the raid is for. and actually i already think there is a invinsible dead line . goes somewhere the day before raid. But raid leaders always do some scrambling for a few more when raid time comes along/. But if you are trying to create that perfect raid Tryle , a dead line is not gonna fix that, its gonna take practice from the guild. Raid leaders as of right now still do a lot scrambling for more people. Its just going to take guild effort and maybe then those perfect raids will start happening. But i think it will come soon. This guild is growing stronger by the min.<br>
<br>
Iceey<br>
