<br>
Being able to post groups the night before cuts down on setup time by so much it is worth the effort of our members to sign up. The worst thing is sitting staring at a wall doing /who lfg or who epic for 30mins after the raid starts. While trying to put together groups.<br>
<br>
Snaake <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=iceey1979>Iceey1979</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/02 9:11:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=180.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amendment to the Raid Template -- Request</span><hr size=1> /agree Snaake <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/utrylebifyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tryle Bifyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 11:06:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=180.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amendment to the Raid Template -- Request</span><hr size=1> That one kael raid that I signed up for just keeps coming to mind where I had no idea I was supposed to sign up the night before and everyone kept telling me... well sorry you didn't sign up in time..  that's what killed me.. I had no idea when &quot;on time&quot; was since I did sign up before the raid started ...  and even though I did get in on the raid, it felt like I was just thrown into a group as a charity case.  I dunno..   I just thought that people new to the guild who don't know the mysterious day before deadline, where it seemed everyone knew but me at the time, would benefit from a sign up deadline so they knew that signing up 6 hours before a raid was about to go underway is too late.  Or at least put SOMEWHERE in like the raiding policy or something that &quot;Hey new folks..  we like to have you signed up for a raid a day ahead of time, blah blah..&quot;<br>
<br>
Lot of the people who been in the guild take this information for granted, but new people don't have the luxury of guild experience to know these things. :)<br>
<br>
Oh well.. beating a dead horse I guess.  I just see it as helpful for new guild members to know these things and not get the experience I got.<br>
<br>
Tryle<br>
52 Wizard<br>
Vazaelle<br>
